cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with improving the robustness of deep neural networks. It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed approach on different datasets. Additionally, the paper involves the use of adversarial samples, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The use of neural networks also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories.
